definitions.definition: A fish of the family Mormyridae , noted for its ability to generate electric fields .
A plownose chimaera , any fish in the not closely related genus Callorhinchus of cartilaginous fish , which uses its fleshy snout to feel for food in sediments and to sense electric fields.
